         <listPerson>
            <person xml:id="pers0042">
               <p>The eldest brother of <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2193.xml"/>Susanna
                     (Annesley) Wesley</persName>, Samuel became in his early twenties a
                  representative of the East India Company in <placeName>Surat, India</placeName>.
                        <persName><ref target="/persons/pers2193.xml"/>Susanna</persName> believed
                  that he was wealthy and that he might bestow some of his wealth on her family,
                  despite a disagreement between him and <persName><ref
                        target="/persons/pers2188.xml"/>Samuel Wesley Sr</persName>. Both of these
                  beliefs proved to be mistaken; cf. Arnold Wright, <hi rend="italic">Annesley of
                     Surat</hi> (<placeName>London</placeName>, Melrose, <date when="1918"
                     >1918</date>). See Clarke, <hi rend="italic">Memoirs</hi> (1823, 244–51; 1836,
                  1:381–94; 1848, 303–13).</p>
            </person>
         </listPerson>
      </body>
